# Redirects — same format on Cloudflare Pages and Netlify.
# One rule per line:   /old-path   /new-path   301
# 301 = permanent (use for migrations); 302 = temporary.
#
# ESSENTIAL FOR MIGRATIONS (e.g. Webflow → Astro): map every old URL to its new
# home so inbound links and SEO ranking survive the cutover. Pull the old URL
# list from the previous site's sitemap, and verify with the pre-launch checklist.
#
# Examples (delete these; add the real ones):
# /old-blog/:slug     /resources/:slug   301
# /home               /                  301
# /pricing.html       /pricing           301
